comments.body:
@lsm5 I am getting it from CentOS
http://mirror.centos.org/centos/7/extras/x86_64/Packages/

But they don't appear to using the spec file from contrib.

@lsm5, appreciate it. To be honest, wasn't expecting to see it in the RHEL repos this early.

Can I get the Red Hat Bugzilla # off you so I can track progress?

Cheers.

@lsm5 appreciate the potential impact of running from Rawhide, which is why I choose RHEL/CentOS/EPEL/OL sources. As you mentioned above, the contrib version of the spec _isn't_ the canonical source.. but where is for the RHEL package?

These packages aren't in the primary OS channels so what is the RHEL process for pulling RPMs into extras?

Is there a location where the upstream RPM .specs that Red Hat consumes live that I can raise bugs against directly?

@lsm5 the Virtualization sig repo you linked to appears to have much _older_ buildah version. (0.5)
[https://cbs.centos.org/repos/virt7-container-common-candidate/x86_64/os/Packages/](https://cbs.centos.org/repos/virt7-container-common-candidate/x86_64/os/Packages/)

I will stick with RHEL and raise with RHEL bugzilla in the future, as mentioned above, didn't realise these packages where in RHEL repos so early (alpha/rc4). Still keen to update the contrib in this repo as I will build from here until RHEL official catches up.
